Class YRCWizard

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Widget

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IYRCComposite, org.eclipse.swt.graphics.Drawable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    YRCAlertDetailsWizard, YRCAlertSearchWizard, YRCGenericWizard

    public class YRCWizard
extends org.eclipse.swt.widgets.Composite
implements IYRCComposite
    The class is used to provide a means to create a wizard. The wizard can be used to perform a complex task in a series of simple steps/processes. The wizard consists of three components:
    • Wizard Page: The UI displayed to the user at each step. A wizard page is of type wizard entity.
    • Wizard Rule: The logical step used to control the flow of the wizard. A wizard rule is of type wizard entity.
    • Wizard Transition: Defines transition from one wizard entity to another.
    • Child Wizard: Branch to separate task and come back
    Author:
    Pramod Varma
    See Also:
    YRCWizardBehavior, IYRCWizardRule, YRCWizardRule2

      • showPreviousPage

        public final boolean showPreviousPage()
        • Applications will call wizBehavior.showPreviousPage()
        • Infrastructure maintains the sequence in which the pages have been displayed.
        • Infrastructure finds the previous page to be shown and displays it.
        • Now pageBeingDisposed(String pageToBeDisposed) is called on all the pages which were shown after the new pageToBeShow and those pages are disposed.

        Example: 
               Original seq: 1 -> 2 -> 2` (Extended) -> 3 -> 4
      Now lets say we call showPreviousPage()
      i)   Page 3 is shown.
      ii)  pageBeingDisposed is called on 4.
      iii) Then once the above is informed to wizBehavior and wizExtnBehavior, the pages
           are actually disposed.

      • showPreviousPage

        public final boolean showPreviousPage(java.lang.String pageIdToBeShown)
        • Applications will call wizBehavior.showPreviousPage(String pageIdToBeShow)
        • Infrastructure maintains the sequence in which the pages have been displayed.
        • Infrastructure finds the page to be shown and displays it.
        • Now pageBeingDisposed(String pageToBeDisposed) is called on all the pages which were shown after the new pageToBeShow and those pages are disposed.

        Example: 
               Original seq: 1 -> 2 -> 2` (Extended) -> 3 -> 4
      Now lets say we call showPreviousPage(2)
      i)   Page 2 is shown.
      ii)  pageBeingDisposed is called on 2` (Extended), 3 and 4.
      iii) Then once the above is informed to wizBehavior and wizExtnBehavior, the pages
           are actually disposed.

      • getFormId

        public java.lang.String getFormId()
        Description copied from interface: IYRCComposite
        Returns the form id of the form.
        Specified by:
        getFormId in interface IYRCComposite
        Returns:
        The unique identifier of a form. It should be a unique id across the application. Note:

        The statndard is to give the fully qualified classpath of the class file. For example, "<Package>.<Class_Name>"

        Form id is used for various purposes. They are:
        • As a unique identifier for the form.
        • In extensibility for adding extended controls.
        • For setting contexts for forms. Setting context enables the key bindings specified for the form.
        • Storing api output templates on the application server.

      • getPageSequenceDefinition

        public java.util.ArrayList getPageSequenceDefinition()
        Utility method to get the sequence of wizard pages defined in the wizard definition. The page ids are returned in an arraylist. The order in the list corresponds to the order in which the pages are to be displayed in the wizard.
        Note: If the wizard definition consists of wizard rule(s) then an empty list is returned since, the correct order of pages cannot be determined.
        Returns:
        An ArrayList of page ids with the order corresponding to the wizard definition.
